# Theming

All design tokens live in `src/index.css`. Do not scatter theme values anywhere else.

## The three regions

- `@theme inline { ... }` - maps tokens to Tailwind utilities (e.g. `--color-primary` -> `bg-primary`) plus the font, radius, spacing and text-style scales.
- `:root { ... }` - **light mode** token values.
- `.dark { ... }` - **dark mode** token values.

## Rules

- When you change a color, update it in BOTH `:root` and `.dark` so themes stay in sync.
- Values use `oklch()` (the shadcn default). Hex is acceptable if you prefer, but keep light/dark consistent.
- Never hardcode colors in components. If a component needs a color, add or adjust a token here and reference it via a Tailwind utility (e.g. `bg-primary`).
- For spacing (padding / margin / gap / space), prefer the named `--spacing-*` scale (`gap-8px`, `p-16px`, `-mt-6px`) over raw numeric steps like `gap-2`. The scale runs `2px`…`32px`; add a new step here if a value is genuinely missing. NOTE: the spacing tokens are pixel-named on purpose — Tailwind's `max-w-*`/`w-*` utilities read the same `--spacing-*` namespace, so t-shirt names (sm/md/lg/xl/2xl…) would collide with the container scale and break every `max-w-*`.
- For text, use the named text-style tokens (`text-h1`, `text-body-sm`, `text-button`) rather than raw `text-sm`/`text-base`.
- Fonts: `--font-sans` (Inter) is the default for body, UI and component titles. `--font-heading` (Fraunces, serif) is bound in `@layer base` to the Display + Heading styles (`.text-display`, `.text-h1`–`.text-h3`), so those pick up the serif automatically — don't add `font-heading` to component titles (they use `text-title`/`text-title-sm` on `font-sans`). `--font-mono` is bound in the same base layer to `.text-label` and `.text-overline`, so all labels/overlines render mono.
- Do not remove existing token names - components depend on them.
